<TITLE> Trade Fair ends with 'up to Tk 300 mln in spot orders' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com)  The Dhaka International Trade Fair ended Sunday with spot orders of at least Tk 250 million, which could rise to Tk 300 million counting the last day's total, commerce minister Faruk Khan said. "The business community feels that a business-friendly government has come to power. Trade fairs are being held in every district of the country," Khan said at the concluding ceremony. The Dhaka International Trade Fair saw a rush of visitors this year, said Export Promotion Bureau vice-chairman Sahab Ullah. He said at least 3 million visited the fair this year compared to 25 million last year. The month-long trade exposition, the largest in the country, was inaugurated on Jan 1. Its duration was extended on Jan 31 for another week. This years' fair saw a total of 486 stalls and pavilions. Products of 10 countries, including the UK, China, India, Pakistan, Thailand and Malaysia, were on display at the fair. Export orders from the DITF amounted to Tk 246.8 million in 2006. But they shrunk to Tk 226 million in 2008 and Tk 199 million in 2009. bdn
